			<div class="content" id="post-content-3608988">
									

<p>I wish I had the time to go back and give this a really thorough copy-edit, because it could seriously use one.</p>
<p>But I'm really glad that I had the time to read this, because it is very good indeed. Turning Kondraki into a character that feels real without rewriting the mythos entirely is quite an achievement. This is keenly observed.</p>
<p>I think the saddest thing is realising that Draven's behaviour, especially towards the very end of the tale, shows hints of the same mental illness that affected his father. A portrait indeed.</p>

