			<div class="content" id="post-content-3613226">
									

<p>I remember when you announced this one on tumblr and I've meant to read it, thankfully somebody brought it up in 19 today or it might've slipped my mind.</p>
<p>This hits&#8230;..really close to home for me. Really, really, <em>really</em> close to home, to the point that I almost couldn't finish it because it was making me remember things I didn't want to. But in the end I think that's precisely why I enjoyed it so much, even if it physically hurt to read. I could write probably an entire essay about why, but a review's not really the place for that.</p>
<p>Upvoted pretty much immediately because holy shit.</p>

